hopobject.body: We'll need to take up references maxoderm south africa Football’s direct and blunt answer to that would be that actually Fifa need very much to be worried about its “cup”, more than anything else. It needs to, not simply because of the logistical difficulties of staging its most valuable tournament in a place of variable infrastructure and unwieldy dimensions. The World Cup itself is a battered object, its status at the top of the sport’s pyramid under probably the biggest threat since a celebrated Brazil team, beamed live and in colour to television sets across the globe, established the competition’s pre-eminence as a sporting spectacle in 1970.
